Sentence 0:
Maximum indicators of SAS synthesis (concentration of extra cellular SAS is 7.2 g/l; factor of emulsification of the cultural liquid 50%; SAS yield from the substrate 50%) have been observed at 60-70% concentration of dissolved oxygen from the saturation level with aerial oxygen (pH 8.0) fractional supply of the substrate by portions each being 0.3-0.4% every 5-6 h to a final volume concentration of 2.4% and with the use of 10% inoculate grown until mid-exponential phase on the medium with 1.0 vol % of n-hexadecane.
